# Last update stamps

The **prototypes hub** table reads each row’s **Last updated** from **`src/app/generated/prototypeHubDates.ts`**.

That file is **generated automatically** when you run **`npm run dev`** or **`npm run build`** (via `scripts/generate-prototype-hub-dates.mjs`): it uses **`git log`** over fixed paths per prototype (Teams demo vs chatbot files). If git is unavailable, it falls back to the **newest file mtime** among those paths.

**Do not edit `prototypeHubDates.ts` by hand.** Touch the relevant prototype sources and run dev/build so the stamp reflects real history.

## Teams prototype

Tracked paths include `TeamsDemoPage.tsx`, `BigPictureTeamsDropdown.tsx`, `BigPictureTag.tsx`, `GlobalTeamsSplash.tsx`.

## Chatbot prototype

Tracked paths include `ChatbotPrototype.tsx`, `ChatOverlay.tsx`, `ChatButton.tsx`.

## Risk Management / Jira mapping prototype

Tracked paths include `RiskManagementJiraMappingPage.tsx`.

## Independent prototype (`prototypes/independent/`)

Still uses **`prototypes/independent/src/prototypeLastEdited.ts`** for its own bundle/hub link if re-added; hub rows are generated as above for app routes.

Hub-only copy/layout changes on `PrototypesHub` do not change timestamps unless you run a build after editing prototype source files.
